    "course_title": "THEORY OF PROBABILITY I",
    "description": "An introduction to measure theoretic probability and stochastic processes.Topics include foundations, independence, zero-one laws, laws of large numbers, convergence in distribution, characteristic functions, central limit theorems, random walks, conditional expectations. Familiarity with basic measure theory (e.g.MATH\u00a0629or721) or concurrent registration inMATH\u00a0721is strongly recommended.",
